    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a buildup of plaque (made of fat, cholesterol, and other substances) inside the arteries that supply blood to your heart muscle. Unlike angina (chest pain), this condition exists without causing noticeable chest pain or other symptoms right now—but the narrowed arteries still restrict blood flow to the heart and pose a risk for future heart attack.",
