    "shortDesc": "Cardiac arrhythmia, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Cardiac arrhythmia, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes an irregular heartbeat where the heart's rhythm is abnormal—it may beat too fast, too slow, or skip beats—but the specific type of arrhythmia hasn't been identified or documented. The heart has an electrical system that controls its rhythm, and when something disrupts this system (such as stress, caffeine, heart disease, or electrolyte imbalances), the heartbeat becomes irregular, which can feel like fluttering, pounding, or feeling faint.",
